---
// cors-preflight-handshake — Chapter 068 Lesson 2, "Standing up R2 — buckets,
// scoped tokens, and CORS".
//
// CORS is the concept students most reliably get wrong because it is invisible
// and asymmetric. This diagram fixes the mental model by making the conversation
// DIRECTIONAL: the browser asks, the bucket answers, and the Next.js function is
// not in the room at all. Three beats, left to right:
//   1. Browser sends the OPTIONS preflight, naming origin + method + header.
//   2. The bucket checks its CORS rule and answers — match → allowed (green),
//      no match → blocked (faint red). The side-by-side outcomes are the point:
//      a valid signature still gets blocked if the rule doesn't admit the ask.
//   3. Satisfied, the browser sends the real PUT with the file bytes.
//
// Plain HTML + CSS phase strip (per the diagrams doc: a sequential strip with no
// parallelism, HTML+CSS preferred). Each panel is a card with a step number, an
// actor tag, a code-styled request/response line, and a one-line caption.
// Chevrons between panels carry the left-to-right read. A greyed "function: not
// in this conversation" tag under the strip nails the "who talks to whom".
//
// Imports reach the shared figures dir three levels up (this file lives at
// components/lessons/068/2/), matching the sibling ArtifactsEnvMap component.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
---

<Figure>
	<div class="cph not-content">
		<div class="cph-strip">
			<!-- Panel 1 — the preflight ask -->
			<div class="cph-panel cph-ask">
				<div class="cph-panel-head">
					<span class="cph-num">1</span>
					<div class="cph-titles">
						<div class="cph-title">Browser asks</div>
						<div class="cph-actor">Browser → R2 bucket</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="cph-wire cph-wire-ask">
					<span class="cph-verb">OPTIONS</span>
					<span class="cph-line">/org/…/files/… preflight</span>
				</div>
				<ul class="cph-fields">
					<li><span class="cph-key">Origin</span> app.example.com</li>
					<li><span class="cph-key">wants method</span> PUT</li>
					<li><span class="cph-key">wants header</span> content-type</li>
				</ul>
				<div class="cph-cap">Before the real upload, the browser asks permission.</div>
			</div>

			<div class="cph-chev" aria-hidden="true">›</div>

			<!-- Panel 2 — the bucket answers -->
			<div class="cph-panel cph-answer">
				<div class="cph-panel-head">
					<span class="cph-num">2</span>
					<div class="cph-titles">
						<div class="cph-title">Bucket answers</div>
						<div class="cph-actor">R2 checks its CORS rule</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="cph-outcomes">
					<div class="cph-outcome cph-allowed">
						<span class="cph-tick">✓</span>
						<div>
							<div class="cph-outcome-title">match → allowed</div>
							<div class="cph-outcome-body">Origin, method, and header are all on the rule.</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="cph-outcome cph-blocked">
						<span class="cph-cross">✕</span>
						<div>
							<div class="cph-outcome-title">no match → blocked</div>
							<div class="cph-outcome-body">The upload never leaves the browser.</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="cph-cap">The bucket&rsquo;s rule is the whole answer — the signature is never consulted.</div>
			</div>

			<div class="cph-chev" aria-hidden="true">›</div>

			<!-- Panel 3 — the real upload -->
			<div class="cph-panel cph-upload">
				<div class="cph-panel-head">
					<span class="cph-num">3</span>
					<div class="cph-titles">
						<div class="cph-title">Browser uploads</div>
						<div class="cph-actor">Browser → R2 bucket</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="cph-wire cph-wire-upload">
					<span class="cph-verb cph-verb-put">PUT</span>
					<span class="cph-line">/org/…/files/… + file bytes</span>
				</div>
				<div class="cph-only-if">Only if step 2 said yes.</div>
				<div class="cph-cap">Satisfied, the browser sends the real PUT.</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="cph-absent" aria-hidden="false">
			<span class="cph-absent-tag">Next.js function</span>
			<span class="cph-absent-note">not in this conversation — it already signed the URL and stepped out</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<Fragment slot="caption">
		The browser asks, the bucket answers, the function isn&rsquo;t in the room. A
		valid signature still gets blocked if the bucket&rsquo;s CORS rule doesn&rsquo;t
		admit the origin, method, and header the browser names.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	.cph {
		margin: 0;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	.cph-strip {
		display: flex;
		align-items: stretch;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 4px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Panels — equal-width cards. min-width:0 lets them shrink proportionally
	   instead of the longest code line forcing one wider than its siblings. */
	.cph-panel {
		flex: 1 1 0;
		min-width: 0;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 9px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, transparent);
		padding: 12px 13px 13px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* The two "browser asks/uploads" panels share a blue rail; the bucket-answer
	   panel — the trust boundary — gets a teal rail to read as the other actor. */
	.cph-ask,
	.cph-upload {
		border-top: 3px solid #0ea5e9;
	}
	.cph-answer {
		border-top: 3px solid #0d9488;
	}

	.cph-panel-head {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: 9px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cph-num {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		display: grid;
		place-items: center;
		width: 22px;
		height: 22px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-size: 0.74rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		color: #fff;
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cph-ask .cph-num,
	.cph-upload .cph-num {
		background: #0ea5e9;
	}
	.cph-answer .cph-num {
		background: #0d9488;
	}

	.cph-titles {
		margin: 0;
		min-width: 0;
	}

	.cph-title {
		font-size: 0.86rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.15;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cph-actor {
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		line-height: 1.3;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 2px 0 0;
	}

	/* Code-styled request / response lines. */
	.cph-wire {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 7px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 7px 9px;
		margin: 0;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-6, #e2e8f0) 55%, transparent);
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
	}

	.cph-verb {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		padding: 3px 7px;
		border-radius: 5px;
		color: #fff;
		background: #6366f1;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cph-verb-put {
		background: #0ea5e9;
	}

	.cph-line {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		margin: 0;
		min-width: 0;
		word-break: break-word;
	}

	.cph-fields {
		list-style: none;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		line-height: 1.25;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
	}
	.cph-fields li {
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cph-key {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #334155);
	}

	/* Panel 2 — the asymmetric pair of outcomes. */
	.cph-outcomes {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 7px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cph-outcome {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: 8px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 7px 9px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cph-allowed {
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #16a34a 14%, var(--sl-color-bg, transparent));
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, #16a34a 42%, transparent);
	}
	/* Blocked outcome is faint — present but plainly the non-default. */
	.cph-blocked {
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #ef4444 9%, var(--sl-color-bg, transparent));
		border: 1px dashed color-mix(in srgb, #ef4444 38%, transparent);
		opacity: 0.78;
	}

	.cph-tick,
	.cph-cross {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		display: grid;
		place-items: center;
		width: 17px;
		height: 17px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		color: #fff;
		margin: 1px 0 0;
	}
	.cph-tick {
		background: #16a34a;
	}
	.cph-cross {
		background: #ef4444;
	}

	.cph-outcome-title {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.15;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cph-outcome-body {
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		line-height: 1.25;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		margin: 2px 0 0;
	}

	.cph-only-if {
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: #0d9488;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Caption line pinned to the bottom of every panel so the three align. */
	.cph-cap {
		margin: auto 0 0;
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		line-height: 1.3;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		border-top: 1px dashed var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		padding-top: 8px;
	}

	/* Chevrons between panels. */
	.cph-chev {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		align-self: center;
		font-size: 1.6rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		margin: 0;
		user-select: none;
	}

	/* The "function isn't here" tag. */
	.cph-absent {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 9px;
		margin: 14px 0 0;
		padding: 8px 11px;
		border-radius: 9px;
		border: 1px dashed var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-6, #e2e8f0) 30%, transparent);
	}

	.cph-absent-tag {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		padding: 4px 8px;
		border-radius: 6px;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1) 35%, transparent);
		text-decoration: line-through;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cph-absent-note {
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		font-style: italic;
		line-height: 1.3;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
		min-width: 0;
	}

	/* Narrow viewports: stack the panels and rotate the chevrons to point down. */
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.cph-strip {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 6px;
		}
		.cph-chev {
			transform: rotate(90deg);
			align-self: center;
		}
		.cph-cap {
			margin-top: 8px;
		}
	}
</style>
